## 10. Breakpoint Changes

PatternFly 6 uses **rem** units for breakpoints instead of pixels:

| Breakpoint | Token | Old (px) | New (rem) |
|---|---|---|---|
| xs | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--xs` | 0px | 0rem |
| sm | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--sm` | 576px | 36rem |
| md | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--md` | 768px | 48rem |
| lg | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--lg` | 992px | 62rem |
| xl | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--xl` | 1200px | 75rem |
| 2xl | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--2xl` | 1450px | 90.625rem |

### Checklist
- [ ] Update any JavaScript breakpoint logic from px to rem (divide by 16)
- [ ] Update any CSS `@media` queries referencing PF breakpoint values
- [ ] Test responsive behavior at all breakpoints

---

## 11. Test Impact & Potential Failures

### Button Test Failures
1. **`aria-disabled` not found**: PF6 uses `disabled` attribute instead of `aria-disabled` for native buttons. Remove tests expecting `aria-disabled="false"` on buttons.
2. **`byText` returns wrong element**: Button text is now wrapped in `<span>`. Use `byRole('button', { name: '...' })` instead of `byText`.

### Select Test Failures
1. **`Cannot find role`**: Menu options may not be found if Popper menu has `aria-disabled`. Pass `{ hidden: true }` option or use `appendTo="inline"`.

### General Test Considerations
- [ ] Update snapshot tests (CSS class names changed from `pf-v5-*` to `pf-v6-*`)
- [ ] Update tests using `data-ouia-component-type` (values changed from `PF5/*` to `PF6/*`)
- [ ] Update tests querying PF CSS classes
- [ ] Update tests for components with changed markup (Accordion, Pagination, NotificationBadge, Wizard, etc.)

---

## 12. Codemods Tool Reference

### Main Codemod
```bash
npx @patternfly/pf-codemods@latest <path-to-src> --v6        # Dry run
npx @patternfly/pf-codemods@latest <path-to-src> --v6 --fix  # Apply fixes
```

### Class Name Updater (CSS classes)
```bash
npx @patternfly/class-name-updater <path-to-src> --v6 --fix
```

### CSS Variables Updater (non-React files)
```bash
npx @patternfly/css-vars-updater <path-to-src>
```

### What Codemods Automate vs Manual Work

#### ✅ Automated by Codemods
- Prop renames (isActive→isClicked, labelIcon→labelHelp, etc.)
- Prop removals (isFlat, isRounded, theme, backgroundColor, etc.)
- Import path updates (deprecated → /deprecated, /next → main)
- Component renames (Text→Content, Chip→Label, MastheadBrand→MastheadLogo)
- Variant value renames (tertiary→horizontal-subnav, light300→secondary)
- EmptyState restructuring (partial)
- Toolbar chip→label renames
- Chart import path changes
- CSS class prefix updates (pf-v5 → pf-v6)
- React token prefix updates
- Interface renames

#### ⚠️ Requires Manual Work
- EmptyState complex layouts (partial codemod coverage)
- Migrating from deprecated Dropdown/Select/ApplicationLauncher to new implementations
- CSS variable overrides that have no 1:1 PF6 equivalent
- Color token replacements (hot pink placeholders)
- Component-level and chart CSS token replacements
- Modal migration from old API to new composable API
- Masthead restructuring (MastheadLogo inside MastheadBrand)
- Test updates for changed markup and selectors
- Breakpoint logic updates (px → rem)
- Custom CSS that references PF internals

#### ❌ No Codemod Available
- Removing fully deprecated components (old Dropdown, Select, AppLauncher, etc.)
- Theming overhaul (all theme-related props removed — no longer React-side)
- DualListSelector migration to new implementation
- Page Header migration to Masthead + Toolbar
- Custom component wrappers around PF components

### Cleanup After Codemods
```bash
# Run AFTER all other codemods are complete:
npx @patternfly/pf-codemods@latest <path-to-src> --v6 --fix --only data-codemods-cleanup
```

---

## 13. Migration Workflow

### Recommended Order
1. **Pre-flight**: Ensure PF5 migration is complete first
2. **Update dependencies**: Change all `@patternfly/*` to v6 in `package.json`
3. **Install**: `npm install` / `yarn install`
4. **Run codemods** (dry run first, then with `--fix`)
5. **Run codemods again** (may need multiple passes)
6. **Run class-name-updater** (`--v6 --fix`)
7. **Run tokens-update** codemod
8. **Run css-vars-updater** codemod
9. **Remove CSS overrides** targeting old PF5 variables
10. **Fix hot pink placeholders** (`--pf-t--temp--dev--tbd`)
11. **Update breakpoint logic** (px → rem)
12. **Build and fix compilation errors**
13. **Run data-codemods-cleanup** (once, after all other codemods)
14. **Update tests** (snapshots, selectors, assertions)
15. **Visual review** (check UI rendering, dark mode, responsive)
16. **Run `yarn i18n`** if translation strings changed

### Key Files to Check in This Template
- [ ] `package.json` — dependency versions and `consolePlugin` metadata
- [ ] `src/components/*.tsx` — all component code
- [ ] `src/components/*.css` — all styles (check for PF class references)
- [ ] `console-extensions.json` — extension declarations
- [ ] `webpack.config.ts` — build config
- [ ] `integration-tests/` — Cypress tests
- [ ] `locales/` — i18n files
- [ ] `.stylelintrc.yaml` — style rules (update PF class prefixes)

---

