<div class="container">

<h1>🔍 PatternFly 5 → 6 Migration Comparison Report</h1>
<p style="color: var(--text-muted);">Generated 2026-05-30 · Base branch: <code>main</code> · Evaluated branches: <code>pf-codemods-053026-1754</code>, <code>semver/goose/052926-2137</code></p>

<!-- ═══════════ CRITICAL CONTEXT ═══════════ -->
<div class="context-note">
  <strong>⚠️ Critical Context:</strong> The base branch <code>main</code> is <strong>already fully migrated to PatternFly 6</strong>.
  All <code>@patternfly/*</code> packages are at <code>^6.2.2</code>, components use PF6 APIs (<code>Content</code> instead of <code>Text</code>),
  and CSS uses PF6 design tokens (<code>--pf-t--</code>). Neither migration branch had meaningful PF5→PF6 work to perform.
  This report evaluates whether each branch's changes are correct and beneficial <em>given that the migration was already complete</em>.
</div>

<!-- ═══════════ 1. VERDICT BANNER ═══════════ -->
<div class="verdict-banner" id="verdict">
  <h2>🏆 Verdict: <code>semver/goose/052926-2137</code> wins by doing nothing — correctly</h2>
  <div class="verdict-score-cards">
    <div class="score-card winner">
      <div class="score">7.0</div>
      <div class="label">semver/goose/052926-2137</div>
      <span class="badge badge-green">WINNER</span>
    </div>
    <div class="score-card loser">
      <div class="score">2.5</div>
      <div class="label">pf-codemods-053026-1754</div>
      <span class="badge badge-red">LOSER</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <h3>Key Reasons</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>The base branch is already on PF6.</strong> Neither branch needed to do migration work. The correct action was "no change."</li>
    <li><code>semver/goose/052926-2137</code> is identical to <code>main</code> — zero diff. It correctly recognized nothing needed to change (or was never modified).</li>
    <li><code>pf-codemods-053026-1754</code> ran pf-codemods against an already-migrated codebase and introduced <strong>4 regressions</strong>:
      <ol>
        <li>❌ Incorrect <code>PageSection</code> → <code>Page</code> rename (semantic layout breakage)</li>
        <li>❌ Corrupted ESLint version to a nonsensical peer-dependency range</li>
        <li>❌ Committed an ESLint cache file (<code>.cache_1l6xbui</code>)</li>
        <li>❌ Added a competing <code>package-lock.json</code> alongside the project's <code>yarn.lock</code></li>
      </ol>
    </li>
    <li>Additionally, <code>pf-codemods-053026-1754</code> upgraded React 17→18, which <strong>conflicts with OpenShift Console's runtime React version</strong> (the project README explicitly states "React 17, not 18 — matches console's React version").</li>
  </ul>
  <p style="color: var(--text-muted); font-style: italic;">Note: Both branches score modestly because neither performed any actual migration work — the migration was already done on <code>main</code>. Scores reflect net impact, not migration effort.</p>
</div>

