<!-- Component API Changes -->
<details>
  <summary>🧩 Component API Changes — PageSection → Page (INCORRECT)</summary>
  <div class="detail-body">
    <h4>What Changed in PF6</h4>
    <p><code>PageSection</code> was <strong>NOT</strong> removed or renamed in PatternFly 6. It remains a valid component at
    <code>@patternfly/react-core</code>. The <code>Page</code> component is a completely different component — it's the
    top-level page wrapper, not a content section.</p>

    <h4>Evidence: PageSection exists in PF6</h4>
    <pre><code>// node_modules/@patternfly/react-core/dist/esm/components/Page/index.js
export * from './PageSection';   // ✅ PageSection is still exported in PF6

// The Page directory contains both:
// - Page.js (top-level page wrapper)
// - PageSection.js (content section within a page)</code></pre>

    <h4>Before (main — CORRECT)</h4>
    <pre><code>import { Content, <span class="diff-add">PageSection</span> } from '@patternfly/react-core';
// ...
&lt;<span class="diff-add">PageSection</span>&gt;
  &lt;Content component="p"&gt;...&lt;/Content&gt;
&lt;/<span class="diff-add">PageSection</span>&gt;</code></pre>

    <h4>After (pf-codemods — INCORRECT)</h4>
    <pre><code>import { Content, <span class="diff-del">Page</span> } from '@patternfly/react-core';
// ...
&lt;<span class="diff-del">Page</span>&gt;
  &lt;Content component="p"&gt;...&lt;/Content&gt;
&lt;/<span class="diff-del">Page</span>&gt;</code></pre>

    <div class="finding finding-bad">
      <strong>Semantic breakage:</strong> <code>PageSection</code> provides sectioned content styling with padding and background.
      <code>Page</code> is the full page shell/wrapper. In an OpenShift Console plugin, the console already provides
      the outer <code>&lt;Page&gt;</code> component. Wrapping content in a nested <code>&lt;Page&gt;</code> will:
      <ul>
        <li>Create a nested page layout (page-within-a-page)</li>
        <li>Lose the section padding and styling that <code>PageSection</code> provides</li>
        <li>Potentially break the overall page layout structure</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <table>
      <tr><th></th><th>pf-codemods</th><th>semver/goose</th></tr>
